techmeme.title: EA reports Q1 net bookings up 3% YoY to $1.3B, above $1.29B est., and forecasts Q2 net bookings of $1.8B to $1.9B, below estimates of $2.01B (Zaheer Kachwala/Reuters)
Google begins rolling out new AI Mode features: Search Live with video, Canvas for planning, and PDF upload, plus AI Mode in Google Lens in desktop Chrome (Abner Li/9to5Google)
Sources: Groq is set to raise ~$600M in a funding round led by Disruptive, which committed more than $300M to the deal that would give Groq a ~$6B valuation (Lizette Chapman/Bloomberg)
Yelp is making AI videos about restaurants, using AI generated scripts and voice-overs based on reviews, incorporating pictures and videos posted by users (Jay Peters/The Verge)
Wag, the pet care tech company once valued at ~$650M following a $300M investment from SoftBank Vision Fund in 2018, has filed for bankruptcy (Stephen Council/SFGATE)
